Sentencas: Tubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are developed with thick (similar to 0.50 mm) La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.5O3 (LSCF)-(Y2O3)(0.08)(ZrO2)(0.92) (YSZ) cathode substrates and thin (6.9 mu m) film YSZ electrolytes.
Titulo: Cathode supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells with nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 electrocatalysts

Sentencas: LSCF is introduced to the thick porous YSZ substrate by impregnating technique, resulting in nanostructured LSCF particles, which are formed at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Cathode supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells with nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 electrocatalysts

Sentencas: The relatively low sintering temperature has effectively eliminated the possible solid-state reaction, which occurs between YSZ and LSCF above 900 degrees C.
Titulo: Cathode supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells with nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 electrocatalysts

Sentencas: The nanostructured electrocatalyst promotes the electrochemical activity, resulting in total interfacial polarization resistance of 033 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C for the single cell.
Titulo: Cathode supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells with nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 electrocatalysts

Sentencas: At the same temperature, the cell has achieved a peak power density of 0.55 W cm(-2), much higher than those reported for the cathode supported tubular SOFCs (about 0.2 W cm(-2)).
Titulo: Cathode supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells with nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 electrocatalysts

Sentencas: The improved performance demonstrates the feasibility of fabricating cathode supported tubular SOFCs with highly active catalysts such as LSCF, Sm0.5Sr0.5Co0.3, Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.5Fe0.2O3 and PrBaCo2O5.
Titulo: Cathode supported tubular solid oxide fuel cells with nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 electrocatalysts
